---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro'
import SignupForm from '@/components/SignupForm.astro'
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Membership | YIMBY Adelaide"
  description="Become a YIMBY Adelaide member and help build a stronger pro-housing voice for Adelaide."
>
  <main>
    <section class="page-hero page-hero--membership">
      <p class="eyebrow">Membership</p>
      <h1>Become a member of YIMBY Adelaide.</h1>
      <p>
        Help build a durable, local, pro-housing organisation that can advocate for more homes,
        better choices, and a fairer Adelaide.
      </p>
      <div class="actions">
        <a class="button" href="#membership">Become a member</a>
        <a class="button button--secondary" href="#email-updates">Subscribe for updates</a>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section split">
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">Two Ways In</p>
        <h2>Email updates and membership are separate.</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="copy-stack">
        <p>
          Subscribing to emails means Action Network can send you updates, campaign actions, and
          invitations. It is the easiest way to stay connected.
        </p>
        <p>
          Membership is a deeper commitment: joining the organisation, backing its work, and helping
          build a lasting pro-housing voice for Adelaide.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section split">
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">Why Join</p>
        <h2>Membership makes the movement harder to ignore.</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="copy-stack">
        <p>
          Signing up is the first step. Membership is for people who want to help YIMBY Adelaide
          become a serious civic voice in planning, transport, housing, and local government debates.
        </p>
        <p>
          Member donations help fund the practical work: research, submissions, community events,
          campaign tools, design, hosting, and the administration that makes advocacy last.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section member-options" id="membership" aria-label="Membership contribution options">
      <article class="member-card member-card--primary">
        <p class="eyebrow">Suggested</p>
        <h2>Membership</h2>
        <p class="member-card__price">Donate what you can</p>
        <p>
          Membership contributions should be donation-based, not a subscription. Give at the level
          that makes sense for you and help get the organisation off the ground.
        </p>
        <a class="button" href="#membership-interest">Register interest</a>
      </article>

      <article class="member-card">
        <p class="eyebrow">Guide</p>
        <h2>Contribution Ideas</h2>
        <p class="member-card__price">$25 / $50 / $100+</p>
        <p>
          These are only suggested one-off amounts. The final payment flow can offer flexible
          donations once we choose the payment provider.
        </p>
        <a class="button button--secondary" href="#membership-interest">Get notified</a>
      </article>
    </section>

    <section class="section values" id="principles">
      <article>
        <span>01</span>
        <h3>Member Voice</h3>
        <p>Members help shape priorities, campaign focus, and the organisation we are building.</p>
      </article>
      <article>
        <span>02</span>
        <h3>Practical Advocacy</h3>
        <p>Member donations fund submissions, research, events, campaign materials, and public education.</p>
      </article>
      <article>
        <span>03</span>
        <h3>Independence</h3>
        <p>We will be transparent about funding and avoid conflicts that weaken public trust.</p>
      </article>
      <article>
        <span>04</span>
        <h3>Local Focus</h3>
        <p>Our work starts with Adelaide: homes near jobs, services, transport, schools, and community.</p>
      </article>
    </section>

    <section class="section split probity-section">
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">Probity</p>
        <h2>We need trust as much as money.</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="copy-stack">
        <p>
          YIMBY Adelaide should be funded by people who want a fairer housing system, not by interests
          seeking special treatment.
        </p>
        <p>
          Before membership donations go live, we will publish clear rules about donations, conflicts
          of interest, governance, and what kinds of support we will not accept.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section application-band" id="membership-interest">
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">Membership Interest</p>
        <h2>Tell us you want to become a member.</h2>
        <p>
          We do not have the membership payment flow live yet. Use the Action Network form to join
          the list now, and we will follow up when donation-based membership opens.
        </p>
      </div>
      <SignupForm compact />
    </section>

    <section class="section split" id="email-updates">
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">Email Updates</p>
        <h2>Not ready for membership? Stay in the loop.</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="copy-stack">
        <p>
          The Action Network signup is for emails and campaign actions. It does not make someone a
          paid member, and it does not collect membership contributions.
        </p>
        <p>
          This separation keeps the first step easy while we design the membership and donation
          infrastructure properly.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
